<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:08AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Franklin County through 445 AM CDT...
At 408 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
east of Altus, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Altus...                          Denning...
Wiederkehr Village...             Alix...
This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 39 and
42.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 600 AM CDT for
west central Arkansas.</instruction>
